	<div class="span-47 last">
	<div class="article main">
	<div id='three-col'> 
	<div class="article-image fl-left">
	
	<img style="; float:left;"
	src="http://images.icnetwork.co.uk/upl/icwales2/jun2010/7/0/surgical-instruments-604200548.jpg"
	height="293"
	width="450"
	border="0"
	alt="Surgical instruments" />

	<p class="article-date">Surgical instruments</p>
	
	</div>
	
	<p>Almost one in 10 patient safety incidents in the NHS Wales results in significant harm to patients, new figures show.</p>
	<p>The reports, which cover the six months between April and September last year, show there were 55 deaths and 68 incidents of &#8220;severe harm&#8221; to patients in health boards and NHS trusts in Wales from such incidents.</p>
	<p>In some parts of the NHS the number of deaths and incidents of severe harm have risen steeply in the last six months.</p>
	<p>Kirsty Williams, leader of the Welsh Liberal Democrats, has called on Health Minister Lesley Griffiths to investigate relatively high death rates in some health boards.</p>
	<div class="article">
	<div class="mpu-ad mpu2">
	
	<script type="text/javascript">//<![CDATA[


